:12,"text":"A common cause of a suprasellar mass in children is a craniopharyngioma.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03464,0.059629,0.075336,0.0861,0.094994,0.098714,0.10428,0.10261,0.098083,0.090926,0.081466,0.073222],"unified_progress":[0.035152,0.063448,0.082044,0.093847,0.099692,0.10383,0.10131,0.098123,0.096873,0.086357,0.07473,0.064593]},{"section":13,"text":"These tumors arise from the remnants of the Rathke's pouch during embryonic development and can cause pressure on the surrounding structures, including the optic nerves.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03529,0.061615,0.079296,0.093301,0.10124,0.10339,0.10785,0.10202,0.095434,0.082991,0.073277,0.064304],"unified_progress":[0.033713,0.067056,0.088067,0.10206,0.10854,0.10729,0.10371,0.096765,0.097503,0.078434,0.063961,0.052909]},{"section":14,"text":"They often have calcifications, which matches the CT scan findings.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040022,0.060517,0.076605,0.087784,0.094609,0.097261,0.10066,0.099165,0.09611,0.090188,0.082624,0.07446],"unified_progress":[0.036933,0.063326,0.080426,0.092233,0.099014,0.1023,0.10129,0.098166,0.096511,0.088208,0.076639,0.064953]},{"section":15,"text":"Another possibility could be a germinoma, but those are more common in older children and young adults.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028259,0.053322,0.068677,0.079465,0.091289,0.097887,0.10639,0.10903,0.10615,0.10106,0.086925,0.071549],"unified_progress":[0.030641,0.059207,0.078363,0.09052,0.096942,0.10814,0.10462,0.103,0.098219,0.094815,0.077426,0.058114]},{"section":16,"text":"They also typically don't have calcifications as often as craniopharyngiomas do.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032332,0.051628,0.066667,0.078279,0.090459,0.097287,0.10596,0.10816,0.10668,0.099407,0.088782,0.074359],"unified_progress":[0.033685,0.059033,0.077118,0